The White House Coronavirus Task Force held a press briefing to provide updates on the ongoing efforts to combat the COVID-19 pandemic. Members of the task force, including Dr. Deborah Birx, Dr. Anthony Fauci, and General Gustave Perna, discussed topics such as rising cases and hospitalizations, the progress of vaccine development, and the distribution plan for vaccines. The briefing emphasized the importance of following public health measures, such as wearing masks and practicing social distancing, and reassured the American people that help is on the way with the development and distribution of vaccines. The task force also reiterated that they do not support another national lockdown and do not recommend closing schools, highlighting the importance of keeping schools open while implementing safety measures.